Is "quick" a palindrome?
A palindrome is when a word or phrase reads identically forward and backward, such as "madam," which reads madam in both directions.
The first two sentences are not palindromes because they have spaces between words. So, if you remove the spaces (which makes them into single words), "quick" becomes "q r k". It does not read the same forwards and backwards, so it is not a palindrome.
Now let's check this for our third sentence: The quick brown fox jumped over the lazy dog.
If we look at each word in reverse order, they don't match. For example:
- q (quick)
- u (jumped)
This means "the" does not match either. So, even with fewer spaces and individual words examined as a whole phrase does not read the same forwards and backwards
